name: The expiration of salt
description:
There you are. Completely up. But what a time we went through together.

I was born on Sept 6. You had a shelf life until September 6. At least, if I can believe the food industry.

It's on your stomach. 'T.H.T. 06 Sep 09 16:54'. What I know for sure about biology is that salt has an unlimited shelf life.

You should check. 06 Sep 09. Then we almost certainly met in 2006.

You stood there for 14 years. Without forsaking a day, always ready. Don't envy your little brother in the kitchen who was allowed to give 'acte de presence' much more often.

You focused on the egg. A task. Never renounced.

You were a nice stable image on my breakfast board. You have experienced many changes there. You stayed.

But now it's really time. You're up. You can't anymore.

It is with respect that I bid you this farewell. Full in the attention of my Insta friends. Who hopefully will give you an unforgettable final greeting.

And what did you get them to look up to? The food industry.

14 years.

They certainly had that there... never...
but never really expected...
